cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation in semantic segmentation tasks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new network structure that involves feature purification, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The semantic segmentation task involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as well as image processing (cs.MM).
